@node "About This Guide"
Being a big fan of the humble Speccy (I also run a Spectrum Emulator on
my Amiga), one day I was sorting through my mass collection of Amiga
magazines, and found some of my old Speccy mags and decided for my next
Public Domain Project to release a mass collection of cheats for Spectrum
games.

Eight months later I released this into the Public Domain, and sent copies
to a few selected PD libraries and Amiga mags. To my surprise, it gets
reviewed in Amiga User International and they rated it 80% !

Despite this, I decided to spend a further 2 months writing this Amigaguide
version, mainly for my own use and here it is! Ten months work. I hope
you appreciate the work that went into this... Now while running your
Spectrum Emulator on your Amiga you now have a quick reference to lots of
lovely Spectrum cheats.
@endnode
@node "Installation on a Hard Disk" "Installation on a Hard Disk"
I recommend you install this guide to your hard-drive. To do this simply
drag the icon to your hard-drive partition/directory containing your
Spectrum Emulator. That way, you will always have it handy should you
need to find a cheat for a particular game, while you are running your
Spectrum Emulator.
@endnode
@node "Printing" "Printing"
Ensure your printer driver on your Workbench is set up correctly. To
print out a particular cheat, Hold down the right mouse button and move the
mouse pointer to the top of the screen and highlight 'Print' from the pull
down menu, and release the right mouse button. The cheat you selected will
now be outputted to your printer (assuming you have one attached!).
